## 3. API DOCUMENTATION

### Standard: Comprehensive API documentation with examples and error codes

**OpenAPI Specification:**
```yaml
openapi: 3.1.0
info:
  title: BizCode API
  version: 1.0.0
  description: |
    # Getting Started
    - Base URL: https://api.bizcode.com/v1
    - Authentication: Bearer tokens (JWT or session)
    - Rate Limit: 100 requests/minute per IP

servers:
  - url: https://api.bizcode.com/v1
    description: Production

paths:
  /clientes:
    post:
      summary: Create new client
      operationId: createCliente
      tags:
        - Clientes
      requestBody:
        required: true
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/ClienteInput'
      responses:
        '201':
          description: Client created
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/ClienteOutput'
        '400':
          description: Invalid input
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'
        '409':
          description: CUIT already exists
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/Error'

components:
  schemas:
    ClienteInput:
      type: object
      properties:
        nombre:
          type: string
          minLength: 1
          maxLength: 255
        cuit:
          type: string
          pattern: '^\d{11}$'
      required:
        - nombre
        - cuit
    
    ClienteOutput:
      type: object
      properties:
        id:
          type: string
          format: uuid
        nombre:
          type: string
        cuit:
          type: string
      required:
        - id
        - nombre
        - cuit
    
    Error:
      type: object
      properties:
        error:
          type: object
          properties:
            code:
              type: string
            message:
              type: string
            details:
              type: object
```

**API Documentation Best Practices:**
- ✅ Complete OpenAPI specification (kept up-to-date)
- ✅ Getting started guide with examples
- ✅ Authentication guide with step-by-step instructions
- ✅ Error code reference with solutions
- ✅ Rate limiting documentation
- ✅ Example requests and responses (curl, JavaScript, Python)
- ✅ Webhook documentation (if applicable)
- ✅ Deprecation policy (how old versions are handled)
- ✅ Versioning strategy (v1, v2, backwards compatibility)
- ✅ Changelog (what changed, when, why)

