## 9. DATA MANAGEMENT & RETENTION

### Standard: Document data classification, retention, and protection

**Data Classification Levels:**
```
Public:
├── No sensitivity
├── Marketing materials
├── Public documentation
└── No special protection required

Internal:
├── Company use only
├── Business processes
├── Performance metrics
└── Standard protection (access control)

Confidential:
├── Customer data (PII)
├── Financial data
├── Contracts
├── Restricted to authorized users
└── Encryption + access logging required

Secret:
├── Passwords
├── API keys
├── Tax IDs (CUIT)
├── Highly restricted
└── Encryption + strict access control + audit

Data Inventory:
─────────────────────
Data Type          | Classification | Retention | Protection
───────────────────┼────────────────┼───────────┼──────────────
Client Name        | Confidential    | 7 years*  | Encrypted
Client Email       | Confidential    | 7 years*  | Encrypted
Client CUIT        | Secret         | 7 years*  | Encrypted
Credit Limit       | Confidential    | 7 years*  | Encrypted
Invoice Amounts    | Internal       | 7 years*  | Access control
Audit Logs         | Confidential    | 3 years   | Immutable, encrypted
Backups            | Secret         | 35 days   | Encrypted, cross-region
User Passwords     | Secret         | N/A       | Hashed (bcrypt)
User Sessions      | Confidential    | 24 hours  | Encrypted
Website Logs       | Internal       | 30 days   | Access control

*Tax requirement (Argentina)
─────────────────────
```

