## 12. ANTI-PATTERNS TO AVOID

- ❌ No documentation (assume people remember)
- ❌ Outdated documentation (worse than no docs)
- ❌ Scattered documentation (in multiple places)
- ❌ Unclear ownership (who maintains docs?)
- ❌ No examples in documentation (theory only)
- ❌ Overly technical for business users
- ❌ Overly simple for technical users (condescending)
- ❌ No version control for docs
- ❌ No review process for docs
- ❌ Compliance docs stored separately from code
- ❌ Risk register never reviewed
- ❌ Post-mortems without action items
- ❌ Action items without owners & deadlines

